_Pi’el_ Past Tense for regular shorushim:
The [[_pi’el_ past tense]] follows the following conjugations for [[regular shorushim]]:
|                | *Singular* |\<                            | *Plural* |\< |
| *First-Person* | זִמַּנְתִּי<br>_zimanti_<br>I invited | \< | זִמַּנּוּ<br>_zimannu_<br>We invited | \< |
| *Second-Person* | זִמַּנְתָּ <br>_zimantau_<br> You [male] invited | זִמַּנְתְּ <br>_zimant_<br> You [female] invited  | זִמַּנְתֶּם <br>_zimantem_<br> You [males] invited  | זִמַּנְתֶּן <br>_zimanten_<br> You [females] invited  |
| *Third-Person* | זִמֵּן <br>_zimein_<br> He invited | זִמְּנָה <br>_zimnau_<br> She invited  | זִמְּנוּ <br>_zimnu_<br> They [male or female] invited  | \< |
For any regular shoresh, you can replace the letters ‎ז, ‎מ, and ן above with the letters of your shoresh to produce the proper conjugations.
